A debounce function is a higher-order function that delays the execution of another function until after a specified wait time has passed since its last invocation, helping to prevent excessive calls in rapid succession.

```javascript
function debounce(func, wait) {
  let timeout;
  return function(...args) {
    clearTimeout(timeout);
    timeout = setTimeout(() => {
      func.apply(this, args);
    }, wait);
  };
}

// Example usage:
function greet(name) {
  console.log(`Hello, ${name}!`);
}

const debouncedGreet = debounce(greet, 1000); // Debounce with 1 second delay

// Simulate usage: Calling debouncedGreet multiple times quickly (e.g., debouncedGreet('Alice'); debouncedGreet('Bob');) will only execute the last call after 1 second of inactivity.
```
